The length of time it takes the moon to go round the
earth, approximately.
\par
About a twelfth of a year, or a little more than four 
weeks.
\par
In our calendar, the months are not all the same length;
they vary from 28 to 31 days. Months are used in calendars
to divide the year up in order to refer to parts of it
more easily; a month is not really a unit of time.